HEADWORD: chiggerflower
<hw>chiggerflower</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an erect perennial of eastern
and southern U. S. (<spn>Asclepias tuberosa</spn>) having showy orange
flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> butterfly weed, orange milkweed, pleurisy root,
tuber root, Indian paintbrush, <spn>Asclepias tuberosa</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
